-- Ex-Spanish Minister Solbes Says Economic Growth to Continue at `Low Rate'
-- B y   F r a n c i n e   L a c q u a
-- 2010-09-29T11:46:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/ex-spanish-minister-solbes-says-economic-growth-to-continue-at-low-rate-.html
Former Spanish Finance Minister
Pedro Solbes played down the possibility of a double-dip
recession.   “We will continue with a low rate of growth,” Solbes said
today in an interview with Bloomberg Television in Brussels. “I
hope that this positive input from Germany will help” other
countries.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Francine Lacqua in Brussels at 
